        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 2:17PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 217 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Federal Heights, or 8 miles northwest of Denver, moving east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northern Denver, western Aurora, northeastern Lakewood, southern
Thornton, southeastern Arvada, southern Westminster, Commerce
City, Northglenn, Brighton, Wheat Ridge, Federal Heights,
Edgewater, Mountain View and Henderson.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
